The paper discusses the evaluation of logic programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of tabling and abstraction techniques also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the focus on declarative programming and efficiency may relate to software engineering (cs.SE).
